51
00:08:25,795 --> 00:08:27,729
'Course not.

52
00:08:27,797 --> 00:08:31,324
- So, what's your name?
- The name's Armitage.

53
00:08:31,401 --> 00:08:34,734
What a sexy back.

54
00:08:34,804 --> 00:08:37,398
- I love broad shoulders.
- Hey!

55
00:08:37,473 --> 00:08:40,874
What was that for?
I was just being nice!

56
00:08:40,943 --> 00:08:43,377
Listen. What's going on here?

57
00:08:43,446 --> 00:08:46,938
Is this somebody's idea of a sick joke?
Annie Oakley here isn't even human.

58
00:08:50,620 --> 00:08:53,453
It's a damn robot.

59
00:08:56,559 --> 00:08:59,460
What's wrong?

60
00:09:00,730 --> 00:09:03,631
What's going on?

61
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:06,635
Spaceport police.
This is their jurisdiction.

62
00:09:15,078 --> 00:09:17,512
In response to the Kelly McCanon incident,

63
00:09:17,580 --> 00:09:20,344
the Martian Police Department
has created T.C.S.,

64
00:09:20,416 --> 00:09:23,180
Technological Criminal SWAT,
to investigate.

65
00:09:23,252 --> 00:09:26,449
Lieutenant Randolph of the M.P.D.
declined further details.

66
00:09:30,493 --> 00:09:32,927
The million-dollar question is:

67
00:09:32,995 --> 00:09:36,089
Just what do we have here,
a woman or a robot?

68
00:09:36,165 --> 00:09:39,225
Sir, results from
my preliminary findings...

69
00:09:39,302 --> 00:09:42,294
are, well, very interesting.

70
00:09:42,371 --> 00:09:45,272
I learned that the, victim...
shall we call her...

71
00:09:45,341 --> 00:09:48,208
is not a human nor a cyborg.

72
00:09:48,277 --> 00:09:50,939
After examining the body,
I concluded she was entirely a robot.

73
00:09:51,013 --> 00:09:54,380
Her body tissue was
of man-made organic origin,

74
00:09:54,429 --> 00:09:56,509
and she functioned through
artificial intelligence.

75
00:09:56,586 --> 00:10:00,022
While no one is capable of
creating a human brain... yet,

76
00:10:00,089 --> 00:10:02,819
her computer brain was very sophisticated.

77
00:10:02,892 --> 00:10:07,727
And, as I mentioned, her physical
construction was created organically,

78
00:10:07,797 --> 00:10:12,131
but it was done using a technology much more
advanced than the Second series models.

79
00:10:12,201 --> 00:10:16,262
I believe that the victim was a
prototype built outside of regulations.

80
00:10:16,339 --> 00:10:19,274
It could also,

81
00:10:19,342 --> 00:10:21,970
mean that there are other
illegal models like her...

82
00:10:22,044 --> 00:10:24,342
running around under our noses.

83
00:10:24,413 --> 00:10:26,347
Yes, thank you.

84
00:10:26,415 --> 00:10:29,851
And now Detective Sylibus
will give his report about the scene.

85
00:10:32,655 --> 00:10:35,015
I... I am Ross Sylibus from
the Chicago Police Department.

86
00:10:41,731 --> 00:10:44,165
The suspects appeared...

87
00:10:44,233 --> 00:10:47,532
I mean, they seemed like they
wanted to transport the body...

88
00:10:47,603 --> 00:10:49,696
without anyone noticing.

89
00:10:49,772 --> 00:10:52,866
Probably to finish
their work somewhere else in private.

90
00:10:52,942 --> 00:10:55,740
Officer Armitage there had been
trailing the suspects...

91
00:10:55,812 --> 00:10:57,746
and then all hell broke loose.

92
00:10:57,814 --> 00:11:00,044
Armitage, can you fill us in?

93
00:11:00,116 --> 00:11:03,051
Well, I trailed the suspects...

94
00:11:03,119 --> 00:11:05,053
and saw they were equipped.

95
00:11:05,121 --> 00:11:07,749
I didn't think
they were carrying a dead robot.

96
00:11:07,824 --> 00:11:09,758
So, what the hell does that mean?

97
00:11:09,826 --> 00:11:12,556
That it was McCanon's impostor
riding the shuttle?

98
00:11:12,628 --> 00:11:14,562
Shut up, Eddie!

99
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:17,224
What did her manager have to say?

100
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:20,133
Well, sir, according to him,
he didn't see any difference...

101
00:11:20,203 --> 00:11:23,730
between the woman he sat with
and the real country-western singer.

102
00:11:23,806 --> 00:11:26,969
And nobody saw her come out
of the arriving terminal.

103
00:11:27,043 --> 00:11:31,707
The only suspicious passenger
he saw was Detective Sylibus.

104
00:11:31,781 --> 00:11:35,273
It seems that the trick for us is
to find out where the real McCanon is.

105
00:11:35,351 --> 00:11:38,115
You know, maybe she's
feeling her wild oats.

106
00:11:38,187 --> 00:11:41,486
Might've found herself
some kind of wild lover.

107
00:11:41,557 --> 00:11:43,491
Christ, Eddie, will you zip it?

108
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:46,494
- Just how was she acting inside the shuttle?
- She acted fine.

109
00:11:46,562 --> 00:11:49,030
She was holding a normal conversation.

110
00:11:49,098 --> 00:11:51,464
Nothing seemed unusual about it to me.

111
00:11:51,534 --> 00:11:54,765
Hell, I wouldn't have been
able to tell her apart from a human.

112
00:11:57,506 --> 00:12:01,636
Are you telling us
that this robot was really McCanon?

113
00:12:01,711 --> 00:12:05,545
You think that prima donna was
a machine from the beginning?

114
00:12:05,615 --> 00:12:10,052
No. I'm saying you can't
distinguish it from a human being.

115
00:12:10,119 --> 00:12:12,280
Hey, yeah, Armitage.

116
00:12:12,355 --> 00:12:16,621
When you realized the corpse was
a robot, you seemed shocked, even upset.

117
00:12:16,692 --> 00:12:18,626
Did you think something was wrong?

118
00:12:18,694 --> 00:12:20,889
Well, did ya?

119
00:12:20,963 --> 00:12:22,897
No, sir.

120
00:12:30,940 --> 00:12:32,874
I hope you like your new place.

121
00:12:32,942 --> 00:12:36,605
It's probably not as nice as you're used
to, but there's a housing shortage here.

122
00:12:36,679 --> 00:12:39,307
